properties.areaDesc: Coastal Waters from Point Pinos to Point Piedras Blancas California out to 10 nm
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 15 at 3:13AM PST until January 16 at 6:00AM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt and seas 8 to 10 feet at 13 seconds
expected. For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 15 to 25
kt with gusts up to 30 kt expected.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Point Pinos to Point Piedras
Blancas California out to 10 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 6 AM to 3 PM PST Thursday.
For the Small Craft Advisory, from midnight tonight to 6 AM
PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
